panels.title: Overview (updates based on top time selection)

targets.rawSQL:
SELECT $__unixEpochGroup(time / 1000, '${interval}') as time, "cs-host" as host, "c-ip" as client_ip, "cs-method" as http_method, "cs-protocol-version" as http_version
	, "cs-uri-stem" as uri, "sc-status-group" as status_code_group, "sc-status" as status_code, "cs-protocol" as request_protocol, "time-taken-in-second" as time_taken_group
	, "x-edge-location" as x_edge_location, "x-edge-result-type" as x_edge_result_type, ua_os, ua_device, ua_browser, ua_category, geo_iso_code, geo_country, geo_city
	, sum("time-taken") as time_taken, sum("time-to-first-byte") as time_to_first_byte, sum("cs-bytes") as request_bytes, sum("sc-bytes") as response_bytes, sum(requests) as requests
FROM "$__table"
WHERE "cs-host" IN (${host:sqlstring}) 
	AND "cs-protocol" IN (${http_protocol:sqlstring}) 
	AND "cs-method" IN (${http_method:sqlstring})
	AND "sc-status-group" IN (${status_code_group:sqlstring})
	AND "hit-cache" IN (${hit_cache:raw}) 
	AND "back-to-origin" IN (${back_to_origin:raw}) 
	AND "time-taken-in-second" >= ${responce_latency}
	AND $__unixEpochFilter(time / 1000)
	AND (event_hour BETWEEN  $__rawTimeFrom('yyyyMMddHH') AND  $__rawTimeTo('yyyyMMddHH')
		OR event_hour = $__rawTimeFrom('yyyyMMdd00'))
GROUP BY $__unixEpochGroup(time / 1000, '${interval}'), "cs-host", "c-ip", "cs-method", "cs-protocol-version"
	, "cs-uri-stem", "sc-status-group", "sc-status", "cs-protocol", "time-taken-in-second"
	, "x-edge-location", "x-edge-result-type", ua_os, ua_device, ua_browser, ua_category, geo_iso_code, geo_country, geo_city;

options.content:
* First byte Latency: The number of milliseconds between receiving the request and writing the first byte of the response, as measured on the server.
* Responce Latency: The number of milliseconds from when the server receives the viewer's request to when the server writes the last byte of the response to the output queue, as measured on the server.

targets.rawSQL:
SELECT $__unixEpochGroup(time / 1000, '${interval}') as time
    , "x-edge-result-type" as x_edge_result_type
    , sum(requests) as requests
    , sum("sc-bytes") as response_bytes
    , sum(case when "time-taken-in-second" >= 1 then requests else 0 end) as lantency_greater_1_requests
    , sum(case when "time-taken-in-second" >= 1 then "sc-bytes" else 0 end) as lantency_greater_1_response_bytes
    , sum(case when "sc-status-group" IN ('3xx', '4xx', '5xx') then requests else 0 end) as error_requests
    , sum(case when "hit-cache" = true then requests else 0 end) as hit_cache_requests
    , sum(case when "hit-cache" = true and "sc-status-group" IN ('3xx', '4xx', '5xx') then requests else 0 end) as hit_cache_error_requests
    , sum(case when "hit-cache" = true then "sc-bytes" else 0 end) as hit_cache_response_bytes
    , sum(case when "back-to-origin" = true then requests else 0 end) as back_to_origin_requests
    , sum(case when "back-to-origin" = true and "sc-status-group" IN ('3xx', '4xx', '5xx') then requests else 0 end) as back_to_origin_error_requests
    , sum(case when "back-to-origin" = true then "sc-bytes" else 0 end) as back_to_origin_response_bytes
    , sum("time-taken") as responce_latency
    , sum(case when "time-taken-in-second" >= 1 then "time-taken" else 0 end) as lantency_greater_1_response_latency
    , sum(case when "sc-status-group" IN ('3xx', '4xx', '5xx') then "time-taken" else 0 end) as error_responce_latency
    , sum(case when "hit-cache" = true then "time-taken" else 0 end) as hit_cache_latency
    , sum(case when "hit-cache" = true and "sc-status-group" IN ('3xx', '4xx', '5xx') then "time-taken" else 0 end) as hit_cache_error_latency
    , sum(case when "back-to-origin" = true then "time-taken" else 0 end) as back_to_origin_latency
    , sum(case when "back-to-origin" = true and "sc-status-group" IN ('3xx', '4xx', '5xx') then "time-taken" else 0 end) as back_to_origin_error_latency
FROM "$__table"
WHERE "cs-host" IN (${host:sqlstring}) 
	AND "cs-protocol" IN (${http_protocol:sqlstring}) 
	AND "cs-method" IN (${http_method:sqlstring})
	AND "sc-status-group" IN (${status_code_group:sqlstring})
	AND "hit-cache" IN (${hit_cache:raw}) 
	AND "back-to-origin" IN (${back_to_origin:raw}) 
	AND "time-taken-in-second" >= ${responce_latency}
	AND $__unixEpochFilter(time / 1000)
	AND (event_hour BETWEEN  $__rawTimeFrom('yyyyMMddHH') AND  $__rawTimeTo('yyyyMMddHH')
		OR event_hour = $__rawTimeFrom('yyyyMMdd00'))
group by $__unixEpochGroup(time / 1000, '${interval}'), "x-edge-result-type";
